@03aliz 1) When you start the Pull Request you'll have an option of which branch you target. It should default to `staging` if you created your branch from `staging` so it's just something to double-check at the start.
2) `npm run test-challenges` is a command you can run from your local directory where all of the FreeCodeCamp files are. There is a test-challenges.js file within the `seed` folder which is run by this command, and it checks that any changes you made don't prevent challenge solutions from passing all the tests of that challenge
3) "Tested changes locally" refers to actually running the local instance of the website using `gulp` and the mongo database, with your changes, so you can see if everything is working as intended.

